VPros and Cons
p751
sg5
VPros:+Long battery life: Place headphones on the base stand and it will recharge the batteries everytime!+Good sound quality with little to no RF interference.+Long wireless range (about four average houses down)+Very rugged (a little bulky, though)Cons:_Base auto-shutoff feature will create an unpleasant sound in the headphones until base receives a audio signal again. NOTE: Headphones don't auto-shutoff._No Line-out on headphones. (for wireless communications to other audio devices)_NOT recommended for those who like it loud._No headphone onboard balance and mono controls._The sound will bleed from the headphones at medium volume which can be heard from across a quiet room. (not recommended if partner is asleep while music volume is set to medium)Overall: It's worth the price.Wishlist:*I wish Sennheiser design a unit the size of a cellphone with a beltclip that uses Koss earbudphones instead of headphones with the mentioned features.*I wish it can "signal" headphones to MUTE while base goes into standby.
