VGreat but always needs maintenance
p1023
sg5
VI have had these headphones for 3 years now. A year ago I would get a lot of popping and static when adjusting the volume. I cleaned the head piece with a can of compressed air and this reduced the problem by 80-90%.Recently the problem returned with the left earpiece cutting in and out when I adjusted the volume. I cleaned the contacts on the volume and tuning dials with  WD-40, and the headphones are working like new again! The sound is much better than my Sony MDRRF985RK.
