sg3
VNeeded to set the TV audio output to FIXED
p1394
sg5
VWe almost sent them back, but now they now work fine.  The issue is the output from our TV was controlled by the TV Volume and Mute.  After researching the web site, I discovered that I could set the audio output to "Fixed".  I give it only 4 stars because I shouldn't have needed to view a video to learn this, it could have been in the included doc...it may also fix the problems of the folks who have hissing issues and distance issues.Explanation:  The earphone controller turns on when it senses the TV sound is ON.  This is a good feature, but if the sound is weak the earphone controller shuts off.  When attached it to an output jack that is controlled by the TV volume, the device sometimes senses the signal and sometimes doesn't.  Cranking up the volume doesn't seem to help...although that is describe as a "fix".  In my Sony TV (and I assume others) the "HOME" menu allows a setting of the audio output to "fixed" .  This provides a consistent signal and the controller doesn't shut off.  Once I set this to "fixed" the control unit turns on immediately when the TV comes on, the distance is much longer and there is no hiss.Bottom line, look for a setting in your TV setup that sets the audio output to "fixed" thus bypassing the TV's volume controls, you may find these headphones much more to you liking.. audio out (RCA jack on back of TV) can be driven through the TV amplifier or provide a  on newere TV's allows
