Vthey are 'on ear' so beware of the real difference in sound leakage between on ear or 'over ear' - it is substantial 2) They are
p1726
sg5
VI bought these headphones a couple years ago and used them for watching TV just before going to sleep while trying not to bother my wife. Comments: 1) There is a lot of sound that leaks from these headphones...they are 'on ear' so beware of the real difference in sound leakage between on ear or 'over ear' - it is substantial 2) They are not comfortable, don't fit well and if you get up and bend over will literally fall off your head. I tried every adjustment to get them to fit with no luck - was always annoying 3) After two and a bit years they stopped taking a charge. I replaced the batteries but no go. I have just replaced the headphones. So, overall not good marks for the RS 120's from my experience....you get what you pay for and in this case do some homework....upgrade to Sennheiser 165 or above, or, for real value for less money I strongly recommend looking at the Sony MDRRF985RK, which are cheaper, far more comfortable and sound (in my opinion) equally as good as the RS 120's.
