sg3
VCrossed in translation: these cans are "on ear."
p1795
sg5
VAs of this writing, this ad labels the RS 120 ii "Over Ear" (in the title) and "over the ears" (in Product Features). This is incorrect, as a quick look at the currently accurate pic will show.The cups of these headphones have no cavity for your ear. Their foam rests directly on the ear, which is why this style is usually referred to as "on ear." Sennheiser's website is consistently clear about this, including in their Technical Data sheet where they use the term, "supra-aural"... 'supra,' loosely translated from the Latin, meaning 'on top of.'Look for the RS 160, RS 170, RS 180, RS 165, RS 175, RS 185 and RS 195 systems and the MM 550-X, the MOMENTUM WIRELESS, and the URBANITE XL WIRELESS for Sennheiser's wireless, "over ear" (AKA "full cup" or "circumaural") headphones, with cups that contact your head 'around' your ears.
p1796
