VWhen I first set out to buy a set of wireless headphones for my viewing pleasure, I wasn't concerned with such notions as crystal clarity, purity of sound, or the complete absence of background white noise.Neither was Sennheiser when they engineered this particular product.But they have concerned themselves with providing a low cost solution for viewers wanting to turn on their television without having spouses and other family members screaming at them to turn down that racket while they busy themselves with such noiseless activities as banging together pots and pans, orchestrating impromptu choirs in your kitchen, or detonating small explosives in the family room.For the price, I feel the quality is fair. If you are concerned with top rate quality of sound without the tedium of constantly adjusting the tuning frequency to just the right notch, you might want to give these a pass.
