VCheck your TV's audio output
p2097
sg5
VNew TV's have digital optical audio output (TOSLINK). The Sennheiser RS 120 only accepts analog. You must buy a TOSLINK to analog converter if you have one of the newer TV. They go for $20-$40. I bought FiiO D3 digital to analog audio converter. You can view the one I bought at:FiiO D3 Digital to Analog Audio Converter With Micca 6ft Optical Toslink Cable - 192kHz/24bit Optical and Coaxial DACThe wireless headphones are great for the price. Now the wife doesn't yell at me for having the TV too loud. I just put on the headset and everybody is happy.I recommend this product to anyone wanting wireless headphones at a great price (and peace at home).
