F5.0
sg3
VThe perfect solution for my silent TV watching and video game playing needs!
p2919
sg5
VI waited to write a review after I had a chance to fully test my new Sennheiser wireless headphones. After several weeks of using them, I must say, I am extremely happy with all aspects of this product! I mainly use them at night, after my fiance goes to bed, so I don't wake her when I watch a movie or play a video game. I am using the headphone adapter to plug the base into the headphone jack of my stereo receiver, which is where I have all audio routed to (TV, CD, PS3, Record Player, Computer, etc...).First off, the headphones sound GREAT, in my opinion! The audio is very clear, and it has a good balance of bass and treble. Neither are overpowering, much like a decent pair of studio headphones...pretty even across the spectrum. I do not notice any "hiss" or feedback when there is audio present, but there is a little hiss when your audio source is silent (like during loading screens for games, or dvd menus). This goes away once audio is playing. I watched a couple of action movies the other night, and the balance between the music, dialog and sound effects was perfect. Also, when playing games, the audio was crisp and balanced. In fact, I could hear a lot of background sounds in the movies/games that I wouldn't have noticed when listening to them without the headphones on.The headphones have a power switch on them, as well as a volume control and a channel tuner. The channel tuner is used for "tuning-in" the reception from the base, in case you are getting static (not for tuning in radio stations, etc...). The volume control works great, and can be used even if the volume on your audio source is turned down low. I have read a few reviews from people who mentioned the volume being adjusted accidentally, when they would lay down on a pillow or something. I have not had this happen yet, but also have not totally tried wearing them while lying down...I have only rested my head against a pillow while on the couch, and have not had any issues like that. The only negative mark I could give it would be that after a couple of hours or more of having them on, the headphones do start to become uncomfortable on your ear. There isn't a lot of padding on them, and they do not fit over the entire ear. But, it isn't so bad for me that I would deduct a star from the review.The range of the signal seems to be very good, and works great for my situation. My front room is fairly large, and I have been able to walk around in it, and into the kitchen without any issues. I would say it is at least 30 feet away from where the base is located, and even when the signal would be passing through a wall. So far, so good. Occasionally, I will get a quick "hit" in the signal when I turn my head a certain way, but it goes away almost instantly. This has happened when I was sitting 5 feet from the base as well, so I'm not sure if it is quick interference from another device, or actually coming from the base. It is definitely not something that is horrible, though, and shouldn't worry anyone thinking about purchasing it, in my opinion.Ultimately, I couldn't be happier with this purchase! The price is definitely right for what you get, especially when compared to other similar products. Plus, being in the video production industry, I have always relied on Sennheiser to deliver quality audio products, and this is no exception. Good clean and balanced audio, high volume, great range, and easy charging make this a great buy.
