VHorrible experience--intermittent hiss, unforgiving static, mediocre range
p2937
sg5
VI was super excited for these, because I've heard nothing but good things about Sennheiser. I expected the audio quality to be top notch.Unfortunately, these headphones were a significant disappointment. I have since returned them.I will say that the audio WAS good--deep bass, full sound, etc--they felt like "studio" headphones.However, the overall experience was terrible, due to several factors:1. They have an awful "power saving" feature that forces the base (but not the headphones!) off, every five minutes. If you are watching a video and put it on pause, you had better remember to turn off the headphones, or you risk hurting your ears with the loud and obnoxious static that appears when the base is off.* Also, you had better make sure there is some audio playing BEFORE you turn the headset on, or you will be subjected to the same horrible static.2. There is an intermittent "hiss", as if it is cycling through frequencies and continually hitting a noisy range. No amount of channel switching or playing with the slider can get rid of this.3. The range is meager. Unlike the Logitech headset that I bought as a replacement, these have trouble reaching through a door. Depending on how I sit, the hissing can become worse.4. The headset was heavy, and a little too tight, making them uncomfortable to wear for long periods.5. They don't have separate microphone and headphone adapters, so it is impossible to use them with standard computer jacks without an additional purchase.I would strongly recommend against purchasing these headphones, unless these five issues are not important to you.* Seriously, who's great idea was it to turn the BASE off, but not the headphones? How does that even save power? There's no battery in the base! The battery's in the headphones! All this useless feature does is train you to constantly second-guess yourself, "Hm...should I turn them off, or will I have audio going in time? Better safe than sorry, I guess..." Ugh.
