VOther people's complaints addressed - UPDATED Dec 2013
p3056
sg5
VI have owned these now for almost two years and they are still working well.  They get daily use of 2 hours on average and show no signs of wear.  I have used them upwards of 6 hours straight without issue.Hiss: Incorrectly tuned on my part.  After some fine tuning, I have no more Hiss.Distance:  Still Great.Comfort: Better.  Either the ear pads have soften from use or my ears now have calluses. :-)Clipping:  The clipping happens after several minutes of no audio connection.  Example is if I turn off the TV and leave the headphones on.  Still I am aware this will happen and adjust for it.  **IMPORTANT** It Does Not Do This While Watching TV/DVD/Streaming.  ONLY if NO Audio is Played for Several Minutes.***ORIGINAL REVIEW BELOW***I read many of the positive and negative reviews before purchasing this product and wanted to address some of the negatives.  I've based my review knowing I purchased an entry to mid level product (on sale) and not the most expensive available.  I use these primarily for TV/DVD/Streaming.Hiss:  There is a hiss when no sound is being supplied to the headphones, but I find it is only during long silences between the primary show and commercials or during the blocked commercials while streaming.  It is not loud and I expected it from the reviews.  It is an acceptable and non-obtrusive hiss.Distance:  I have no troubles walking anywhere in my house (two stories) and find no diminishing of the quality of sound.Comfort:  They are comfortable and light weight.  I do find after an hour or more you can feel them against your ears more and it can be slightly distracting.  However, considering the convience of being able to watch a movie loudly without disturbing the household, it is a small price to pay.Clipping:  I haven't tried to determine why they do this, but at some point it does occasionally make a clipping noise.  It is slightly annoying, but not so loud as to injure.  IMPORTANT- it doesn't do this during the show.  Only during dead space.Base:  Easy to set up and easy to use.  No problems.This is all I currently have.  I have only had these for two weeks, but use them regularly.  I would recommend purchasing one at the reduced price.  Don't know if I would pay retail for them. I am considering a second one.Hope this helps.
